The paper proposes a method for fair machine learning using neural networks and continuous variables. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of adversarial neural networks, which is a common technique in computer security (cs.CR). The Hirschfeld-Gebelein-Renyi coefficient is a measure of correlation, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper discusses regression models, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV).
